# Whitelist approach: everything's excluded except the directories that
# actually feed the build. Keeps the context small and prevents new
# top-level files (helm values, k8s manifests, docs) from silently
# bloating it.
*
!image
!image/**
!tools
!tools/**
# Dockerfile is always sent via -f, but also include for consistency.
!Dockerfile
# Re-exclude trash even inside allowed paths.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.log
**/*.swp
**/WindowsServer/
# Gitignored local-only values (also usually secret) — belt-and-braces.
values-*.yaml
.env
.env.*
